Taraba State governor, Arc. Darius Ishaku, has described the defection of Cross River State governor, Ben Ayade, to the All Progressive’s Congress (APC) as embarrassing and shocking to the People’s Democratic Party (PDP).  Governor Ishaku Fielding questions from State House Correspondents after meeting with the Chief of Staff to the President, Professor Ibrahim Gambari, in Abuja to discuss issues surrounding Mambilla Hydropower among other issues, regretted that inspite of the interventions of the PDP National Reconciliation Committee, Gov. Ayade still defected, expressing optimism that more PDP Governors will not defect to the APC.  Our Correspondent, Raliat Adenekan reports that the Governor while speaking on the spate of insecurity in Taraba said the issues is being tackled.